## Proposed Changes

### Infrastructure & Database Setup
* Initialize Next.js app.
* Set up Supabase client.
* **Database Schema:**
  * `users` / `practitioners`: Auth handling.
  * `clients`: id, name, contact info, notes, created_at.
  * `sessions`: id, client_id, start_time, end_time, summary.
  * `manuals`: id, title, description.
  * `manual_sections`: id, manual_id, chapter, content (Markdown/HTML), order_idx.
  * `annotations`: id, section_id, type ('highlight'|'note'), scope ('client'|'global'), client_id (optional), session_id (optional), content, exact_text_reference, position_data.

### Authentication Layer
#### [NEW] `src/app/login/page.tsx`
Practitioner secure login page using Supabase Auth.
#### [NEW] `src/middleware.ts`
Route protection to ensure only authenticated users can access the app and its data.

### Layout & Global State
#### [NEW] `src/components/layout/AppLayout.tsx`
Sidebar with navigation (Manuals, Clients, Review Notes).
#### [NEW] `src/store/useSessionStore.ts`
Zustand global store to hold the *Active Session* state (Current Client, Start Time). Floating widget indicating an active session so she always knows who the current notes are saving for.

### Client CRM
#### [NEW] `src/app/clients/page.tsx`
Directory of all clients.
#### [NEW] `src/app/clients/[id]/page.tsx`
Client profile showing session history and aggregated highlights/notes chronologically.

### Manual Viewer & Navigation
#### [NEW] `src/app/manuals/page.tsx`
Grid view of the 6 manuals.
#### [NEW] `src/app/manuals/[id]/page.tsx`
Table of contents and chapters list for a specific manual.
#### [NEW] `src/app/manuals/[id]/read/page.tsx`
The core reading interface. Touch-optimized scrolling, large interactive touch targets.
#### [NEW] `src/components/manual/ContentRenderer.tsx`
A component to render the parsed text and diagrams. Intercepts text selection to show a contextual popover ("Highlight", "Add Note").

### Annotation System
#### [NEW] `src/components/manual/AnnotationPopover.tsx`
Appears directly above selected text on touch/click. Options depend on `useSessionStore.ts` active state (e.g., Client Highlight vs Global Highlight, adding Notes). Also includes options to **delete an existing highlight or note** when tapping on it.
#### [NEW] `src/app/review/page.tsx`
A dashboard to view practitioner notes collected over time to decide what to edit permanently.

### Manual Parsing Protocol (To Do)
* **Scripts:** A Python or Node-based script will need to be written to ingest the 6 PDFs. The exact implementation details of this script will be determined once the user uploads the PDFs for analysis, focusing on maintaining chapter structure and inline diagrams.

### Editing System
#### [NEW] `src/app/manuals/[id]/edit/page.tsx`
A rich text editor interface for modifying the raw `manual_sections` content post-session.

## Verification Plan
### Manual Verification
* Log in as practitioner.
* Create a client and "Start a Session" with them.
* Open a manual, select text, and apply a Client Highlight.
* End Session. Verify the highlight appears on the Client's CRM profile.
* Add a Global Note to a manual. Verify it appears in the Review Dashboard.
* Use the Edit Mode to change a sentence in the manual. Verify the change persists in the reading view seamlessly.
